-- Taiwan Stocks: Foxconn Technology, King Yuan, Powertech, UMC
-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 2012-03-20T06:20:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/taiwan-stocks-foxconn-technology-kuoyang-construction-umc.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  dropped 0.9 percent to 7,972.70.  Foxconn Technology Co. (2354)  (2354 TT) fell 2.8 percent to
NT$122, the lowest since Feb. 7, after it was cut to sell from
hold at Berenberg Bank.  King Yuan Electronics Co. (2449)  (2449 TT) declined 1.7 percent to
NT$11.30. Its board approves a plan to seek NT$3.8 billion ($129
million) of five-year syndicated loans to replenish working
capital, according to a company statement to the Taiwan stock
exchange.  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT) lost 1.8 percent to
NT$55.60 after it was cut to neutral from overweight at
JPMorgan.  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT) rose 0.7 percent to
NT$15. The chipmaker booked a gain of NT$160.5 million from
selling 7.31 million shares in Springsoft Inc., it said in a
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  